    "expect_stage": "complete",
    "expect_profile": {
      "goal": "change my goal to reduce cancellations"
    },
    "_note": "Known parser limitation: strips 'actually, ' prefix but stores remaining text verbatim, including meta-instruction phrasing ('change my goal to'). This test asserts current behavior, not ideal behavior. Future: strip intent prefixes ('change my goal to', 'set it to', etc.) before storing. Do not change expect_profile without fixing the parser. ASYMMETRY: the 'ACTUALLY make that X' phrasing (onboard_correction_caps) correctly strips both the 'ACTUALLY ' and 'make that ' prefixes and stores only 'X'. The comma variant ('actually, change my goal to X') does not strip the intent clause. Parser behavior is phrasing-dependent \u2014 fix should normalize both paths."
  },
